Package: rnirs
Type: Package
Title: Locally Weighted PLS Regression and Discrimination
Version: 1.0-10
Author: Matthieu Lesnoff <matthieu.lesnoff@cirad.fr>
Maintainer: Matthieu Lesnoff <matthieu.lesnoff@cirad.fr>
Description: Statistical tool box focusing on locally weighted prediction
  methods: regression for quantitative responses and discrimination for qualitative responses. 
  The predictive models can use partial least squares dimension reductions or other methods.
  The package is primarily dedicated to near infrared spectral data 
  but can be used for many other types of data.
Depends: R (>= 3.0.0)
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Imports: scales, signal, data.table, FNN, ggplot2, gridExtra 
Suggests: knitr, rmarkdown
URL: https://github.com/mlesnoff/rnirs
License: GPL (>= 2)
LazyData: yes
